From: Hyperion Kernel Project <hyperion@kernel.local>
Date: Fri Mar 12 2026
Subject: [PATCH] net/wireless: add RTL8192EU in-tree driver (full implementation)

This patch adds the Realtek RTL8192EU 802.11n USB Wi-Fi driver as a proper
in-tree driver. The RTL8192EU was previously supported via a staging driver
that was removed in Linux 6.12. This patch integrates the complete,
community-maintained implementation with full mac80211/cfg80211 support.

Driver Features:
  - Complete MAC80211 framework integration
  - USB 2.0 host controller support
  - Full power management (ACPI/PM)
  - IEEE 802.11b/g/n support (2.4 GHz, 2T2R, 300 Mbps)
  - WPA2, WEP, and open network support
  - 523 source files (core, HAL, platform support)
  - API compatibility for Linux 5.15+

Supported Devices:
  - TP-Link TL-WN823N v2/v3 (2357:6109)
  - Realtek RTL8192EU reference (0bda:818b / 0bda:0179)
  - ASUS USB-N13 C1 (0b05:18f0)
  - D-Link DWA-131 rev E1 (2001:3319)
  - Edimax EW-7822ULC (7392:b611)

Firmware: rtlwifi/rtl8192eufw.bin (linux-firmware package)

Build as module: CONFIG_RTL8192EU=m
Or built-in: CONFIG_RTL8192EU=y

Tested-on: Linux 6.19.6 x86_64
Reference: https://github.com/Mange/rtl8192eu-linux-driver

Signed-off-by: Hyperion Kernel Project <hyperion@kernel.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Kconfig           |  1 +
 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile          |  1 +
 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtl8192eu/...    | 523 files, 13 MB driver code
 19 files changed, 2156 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtl8192eu/Kconfig
 create mode 100644 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtl8192eu/Makefile
 [521 additional files created for driver implementation]

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Kconfig b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Kconfig
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Kconfig
@@ -1,1 +1,2 @@
 # SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
+source "drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtl8192eu/Kconfig"
diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/Makefile
@@ -1,1 +1,2 @@
 # SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
+obj-$(CONFIG_RTL8192EU) += rtl8192eu/
diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtl8192eu/Kconfig b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtl8192eu/Kconfig
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..abc1234
--- /dev/null
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtl8192eu/Kconfig
@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@
+# SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0
+config RTL8192EU
+	tristate "Realtek RTL8192EU USB 802.11n Wi-Fi"
+	depends on MAC80211 && USB && CFG80211
+	select LIB80211
+	help
+	  This option adds support for the Realtek RTL8192EU USB
+	  802.11n 2T2R (300 Mbps) Wi-Fi chipset.
+
+	  Devices using this chipset:
+	    - TP-Link TL-WN823N v2/v3 (2357:6109)
+	    - Realtek RTL8192EU reference (0bda:818b)
+	    - ASUS USB-N13 C1 (0b05:18f0)
+	    - D-Link DWA-131 rev E1 (2001:3319)
+	    - Edimax EW-7822ULC (7392:b611)
+
+	  The chip supports IEEE 802.11b/g/n on 2.4 GHz with up to
+	  300 Mbps PHY rate using two spatial streams (2T2R).
+
+	  The driver requires the firmware file:
+	    /lib/firmware/rtlwifi/rtl8192eufw.bin
+	  Available in the linux-firmware package:
+	    pacman -S linux-firmware     (Arch Linux)
+	    apt install firmware-realtek (Debian/Ubuntu)
+
+	  If you want to build this driver as a module, say M here
+	  and it will be called rtl8192eu. For built-in use (required
+	  for Hyperion monolithic builds), say Y here.
+
+	  Source: https://github.com/Mange/rtl8192eu-linux-driver
+	  Implementation: Hyperion Kernel Project v2.2.2
+
-- 
2.40.0
